    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;</span><strong>Sale</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">means the completion of an agreement for the purchase of all the issued share capital of the Company (to the extent not already owned by the purchaser or by persons acting in concert with (as that phrase is defined in section 1(3) of the Irish Takeover Panel Act, 1997), or a Connected Person of, the purchaser), or the acceptance of an offer as a result of which the offeror becomes entitled or bound to acquire all such shares in accordance with the Companies Act;</span></p>
    <p><strong>"Service Agreement"</strong> <span style="font-weight: 400;">means the form of service agreement set out in Schedule 3;</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;</span><strong>Shares</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">means the Ordinary Shares and any other class of ordinary shares issued by the Company from time to time;</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;</span><strong>Shareholders</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo; and each a</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;</span><strong>Shareholder</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">means any registered holder of one or more Shares from time to time and "Shareholding" shall have the corresponding meaning and shall be interpreted as a shareholding in the Company;</span></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;</span><strong>Subsidiaries</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">has the meaning given in section 7 of the Companies Act; and</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&ldquo;</span><strong>Transfer</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">means, in relation to any Share, to transfer the entire legal and beneficial interest in that Share free from all claims, liens, charges, encumbrances and equities and together with all rights attached or accruing to that Share.</span></p>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>WORDS AND PHRASES</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Any reference to any provision of any legislation shall include any modification, re-enactment, amendment or extension thereof.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The masculine gender shall include the feminine and neuter and the singular number shall include the plural and vice versa and words importing persons shall include firms or companies.&nbsp; Words such as &ldquo;hereunder&rdquo;, &ldquo;hereto&rdquo;, &ldquo;hereof&rdquo; and &ldquo;herein&rdquo; and other words commencing with &ldquo;here&rdquo; shall unless the context clearly indicates to the contrary refer to the whole of this agreement and not to any particular Section or Clause thereof.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Save as otherwise provided therein any reference to a Clause or schedule shall be a reference to a Clause or schedule (as the case may be) of this Agreement and any reference in a Clause to a paragraph or sub-paragraph shall be a reference to a paragraph or sub-paragraph of the Clause or paragraph in which the reference is contained unless it appears from the context that a reference to some other provision is intended.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Clause headings and captions to the Clauses in this Agreement are inserted for convenience or reference only and shall not be considered a part of or affect the construction or interpretation of this Agreement.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Words and phrases the definitions of which are contained or referred to in the Companies Act shall be construed as having the meaning thereby attributed to them.&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">References to any document (including this Agreement) are references to that document as amended, consolidated, supplemented, novated or replaced from time to time.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">References to the Shareholders include their respective successors and permitted assigns in respect of the Shares held by those Shareholders.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">References to persons shall include any individual, any form of body corporate, unincorporated association, firm, partnership, joint venture, consortium, association, institution, organisation or trust (in each case whether or not having a separate legal personality).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">References to writing or similar expressions includes, unless otherwise specified, transmission by facsimile and email.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>BUSINESS OF THE COMPANY</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The business of the Company shall be </span><strong>{{companyBusiness}} </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">(the &ldquo;</span><strong>Business</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;).&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The business of the Company shall be the Business and any other commercial activities which are considered to be in the interests of the Company as determined in accordance with Clause 9 </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">(Conduct of the Company&rsquo;s Affairs)</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The central management and control of the Company shall be exercised in Ireland and each of the Shareholders shall use their best endeavours to ensure that the Company is treated by all relevant authorities as being resident in Ireland for taxation and other purposes.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Shareholders shall procure that the Constitution shall (if required) be amended as shall be necessary to reflect the provisions of this Agreement relating to the appointment of Directors and the transfer of Shares.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>COMPLETION AND RELATED MATTERS</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Completion shall occur immediately following the signing of this Agreement at the offices of the Company or such other place as the Shareholders may agree (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Completion Date</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">On the Completion Date, the shareholders shall procure or cause to be taken the following steps at either directors&rsquo; or shareholders&rsquo; meetings of the Company:</span></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the designation of&nbsp; {{companyDirector}} as&nbsp; a Director of the Company and any subsidiaries;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the employment of {{employee}} as a </span><strong>{{employeeJob}} </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">and the signing of the Service Agreement by both {{employee}} and the Company; and&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">selection of a suitably qualified individual or body corporate as secretary of the Company (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Company Secretary</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) and any subsidiaries pursuant to Section 129 of the Companies Act.</span></li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>APPOINTMENT OF DIRECTORS</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Unless otherwise determined by an ordinary resolution of the Company in general meeting, the number of directors shall be not be less than two or more than five.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">For as&nbsp; long as {{companyDirector}} holds Shares, {{companyDirector}} shall be entitled to have two Directors appointed to the Board at its sole discretion;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Any appointment or removal of a Director, or vesting or adjustment of the number of votes vested in a Director pursuant to this Clause 6(</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Appointment of Directors</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">), shall be effected by delivering written notice thereof to the Company Secretary of the Company, with a copy to the other Shareholders and shall take effect on the date that such notice is deemed by Clause 25 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Notices</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) to have been received by each of the Company Secretary and the other Shareholders or, if later, the date specified in that notice.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Shareholders shall be entitled to appoint additional Directors, subject to Clause 6.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Shareholder may, by delivering written notice to the Company, with a copy to the other Directors, appoint one alternate director, from amongst the other Directors or approved by the Board, for each Director appointed by him to represent such Director at meetings of the Board which such Director is unable to attend (an &ldquo;</span><strong>Alternate</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;), and such Shareholder or Shareholders may at their discretion terminate such appointment by similar written notice to the Company and the other Directors and, whether at the same time or later, appoint a replacement Alternate approved by the Board, or from amongst the other Directors. Any Alternate appointed pursuant to this Clause 6 </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">(Appointment of Directors) </span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">shall be entitled to receive notices of all meetings of the Directors and to attend, speak and vote at any such meeting at which the Director for whom he has been appointed Alternate is not present and shall be subject in all respects to the terms, conditions and characteristics existing with reference to the Director for he is appointed Alternate.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">An Alternate shall not be taken into account in reckoning the minimum or maximum number of Directors allowed for the time being pursuant to this Clause 6 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Appointment of Directors</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) but he shall be counted (more than once if representing more than one Director) for the purpose of determining whether a quorum is present at any meeting of the Directors attended by him at which he is entitled to vote.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">One person may act as an Alternate to more than one Director and while he is so acting shall be entitled to a separate vote for each Director he is representing and if, he is himself a Director, his votes or votes as an Alternate shall be in addition to his own vote.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>PROCEEDINGS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Company shall not enter into any contract or transaction whereby its Business will be controlled and/or managed otherwise than by the Board.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board shall at all times comply with the provisions of Clause 11 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shareholders&rsquo; Consent</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) hereof.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board shall meet not less than once in every three months (one meeting per each quarter year) in accordance with and subject to the Constitution.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Unless otherwise agreed in writing by all of the Directors, the Company shall procure that not less than five clear days&rsquo; notice of all meetings of the Board shall be given to each Director.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The quorum for the meetings of the Board shall be two Directors present in person or by alternate. Such Directors must each have been appointed by a different Shareholder.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If within half an hour from the time appointed for any Board meeting a quorum is not present the meeting shall stand adjourned to the next following Business Day at the same time and place and the Directors then present.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Director of the Board may participate in a meeting of the Directors by means of telephonic or other similar communication whereby all of the Directors can hear each other speak and participation in a meeting in this manner shall be deemed to constitute presence for the purposes of Clause 7.5 above. The Board shall take all reasonable steps to make such telephonic or other similar means of communication available to any Director who requests them for the purposes of a Board meeting.&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board may delegate any of its powers (including without limitation the sealing of documents of a class approved by the Board for issue under the seal of the Company) to committees consisting of such member or members of the Board of Directors as it thinks fit and any committee so formed shall, in exercise of the powers so delegated, conform to any regulations, and operate within any written terms of reference, that may be imposed on it by the Board from time to time.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The post of chairman of the Directors for each meeting of the Directors will be decided by the Directors at each such meeting. The chairman shall not have a casting vote.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>BOARD MATTERS</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Any decision by the Company and/or any of its subsidiaries shall require the approval of a majority of Directors present (in accordance with Clause 7 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Proceedings of the Board of Directors</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) at a meeting of the Board properly convened and held.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a deadlock of the votes of the Directors under Clause 8.1 and the deadlock remains unresolved for a period of three business day, the provisions of Clause 19 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Deadlock</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) will apply.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>CONDUCT OF THE COMPANY&rsquo;S AFFAIRS</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Business shall be managed by the Board, who shall have the power to run and manage the Company and to execute all acts and operations related to its corporate purpose save for such acts or operations which are, by the Companies Act, this Agreement or the Constitution, required to be exercised by the Company in general meetings save in particular that the actions listed in Clause 11 </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">(Shareholders&rsquo; Consent)</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> shall not be carried out unless approved in advance in accordance with Clause 11 </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">(Shareholder&rsquo;s Consent), </span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">provided that this Clause 8</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br /></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">(</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Conduct of the Company&rsquo;s Affairs</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) or Clause 11 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shareholder&rsquo;s Consent) </span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">shall not prevent or restrict the granting by the Company of security to any party providing financial support to the Company under which such party may be entitled to appoint a receiver or similar officer having powers in respect of the management.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Shareholders shall each be entitled to examine and inspect (with the assistance of an adviser) the books, accounts and records to be kept by the Company and to be supplied with all relevant information in such form as they may reasonably require to keep each of them properly informed about the Business of the Company and generally to protect their interests.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board shall maintain, or cause to be maintained, full and correct books and financial records of the Company. The books and financial records shall be maintained in such a manner as to clearly show a true, accurate and separate record of all costs and expenses incurred, all charges made, all credits made and received and all income derived in connection with the Business sufficient to obtain an unqualified opinion from the auditors as to the financial position and results of operation of the Company.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board shall prepare, or cause to be prepared, all income tax, corporate, statutory and other returns of the Company and cause the same to be filed in a timely manner and in any event so as to avoid the payment of interest and/or penalties. The Company shall furnish to each of the Shareholders a copy of each such return as soon as each such return has been filed, together with any schedules and tax receipts or other information which the Shareholders may require in connection with their own tax affairs.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The provisions of Clause 6 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Appointment of Directors</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">), Clause 7 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Proceedings of the Board of Directors</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">), Clause 8 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Board Matters</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) and Clause 9 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Conduct of the Company&rsquo;s Affairs</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) shall apply </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">mutatis mutandis</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to the boards and board meetings of any subsidiaries of the Company.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>MEETINGS OF THE SHAREHOLDERS</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No business shall be transacted at any meeting of the Shareholders (or any adjourned meeting of the Shareholders) unless a quorum of the Shareholders is present at and throughout the meeting.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The quorum at any meeting of the Shareholders (and any adjourned meeting of the Shareholders) shall be two persons both of whom are holders of Relevant Shares, present in person or by proxy or, being a corporation, by a duly authorised representative.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If a quorum is not present when the relevant business is to be transacted at a meeting of the Shareholders, that meeting shall be adjourned to a day not earlier than ten Business Days and no later than twenty Business Days from the date of such meeting and provided that forty-eight hours&rsquo; notice has been given to all Shareholders, a quorum at such meeting shall consist of an authorised representative of any two of the Shareholders.&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Minutes of all meetings of the Shareholders shall be prepared as soon as practicable following such meetings by the secretary of the meeting and, copies thereof distributed to each of the Directors and the Shareholders within fourteen days of each meeting.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Company Secretary shall issue a notice convening any meeting of the Shareholders and all relevant papers for such meetings shall be sent to all Shareholders in good time prior to the relevant meeting and in any event so as to ensure that they are received not less than forty eight hours prior to the timed fixed for such meeting.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a deadlock or dispute arising between the Shareholders the terms of Clause 19 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Deadlock</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) will apply.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>SHAREHOLDERS&rsquo; CONSENT</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Reserved Matters</strong></li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Except as otherwise required by the Companies Act, any decision relating to any of the following matters (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Reserved Matters</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) shall require the prior written consent or the vote in favour of Shareholders controlling more than 70% of the Relevant Shares at a general meeting of the Company properly convened and held:</span></p>
    <ol>
    <ol>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">creation, issue or allotment, or agreement to create, issue or allot any share or loan capital of the Company (including without prejudice any class or series of equity shares having rights as to dividends or payments upon liquidation, dissolution or winding up) ranking in any respect </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">pari passu</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> with or superior to the Shares;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">consolidation, sub-division or alteration of any of the rights attaching to any of the Shares or reduction of its share capital or repayment of any amount standing to the credit of any share premium account or capital redemption reserve fund or capitalisation of any reserves or buy back of any Shares or otherwise reorganising its share capital in any way or creating any new class of shares;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">entering into any leases of real property with Connected Persons or making any amendments to any leases of real property previously entered into by the Company with Connected Persons;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">creating any borrowings by the Company or any of its subsidiaries or incurring any debt exceeding &euro;20,000;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">creating any lien or encumbrance over the issued share capital of the Company;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">making, giving, entering into or incurring a guarantee, indemnity, undertaking, other material commitment on capital account or unusual liability of the Company;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">entering into any onerous or unusual contract arrangement or understanding or any contract capital commitment or expenditure materially affecting the business or assets of the Company;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">entering into any capital commitment or expenditure, where any one item exceeds &euro;20,000;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">acquiring any asset outside the scope of the annual budget of the Company with a value exceeding &euro;20,000;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">disposing of a majority of the issued share capital of the Company or any substantial or material part of its fixed assets or business;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">passing any resolution of the members of the Company in general meeting the effect of which would be to alter in any material way the nature of such company and/or its business or envisaged by this Agreement;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">increasing or decreasing the size of the Board;&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">appointing a director; and</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">appointing or removing any employee or consultant earning in excess of &euro;20,000 and/or having a management function.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nothing in this Clause 11 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shareholders&rsquo; Consent</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) shall operate to release or otherwise exempt the Company or the Shareholders from the requirement under the Companies Act or any other legal provision, where appropriate, to approve any of the above matters by way of shareholders resolution in addition to approval by the Directors and the responsibility to obtain such shareholder approval will rest with the Directors.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The provisions of this Clause 11 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Reserved </span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Matters) shall apply </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">mutatis mutandis</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to any subsidiaries of the Company.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>DIVIDEND AND DISTRIBUTION POLICY</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Distributions by way of dividend shall only be made with the approval of the Shareholders and to the extent permitted by law.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In determining whether any dividend should on any occasion be declared or paid by the Company, the Board shall have regard </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">inter alia</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to the cashflow and working capital requirements of the Company and any subsidiaries.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Company shall not make any dividend payments for the first two Financial Years following the Company&rsquo;s incorporation.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Any Intellectual Property Rights which arise in the course of the Company&rsquo;s activities shall belong to the Company.</span></p>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>DEALING IN SHARES</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In all situations, other than those described in Clauses 15 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compulsory Transfers &ndash; Drag Along</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) 16 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compulsory Transfers &ndash; Tag Along</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) and 18 </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">(Allocation of Shares &ndash; Performance Incenttive)</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">, a Shareholder may only Transfer his Shares in the manner set out in this Clause 14 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dealing in Shares</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) and the Constitution.</span></p>
    <ol>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Shareholder wishing to Transfer of Dispose his shares (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Seller</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) must give notice (a &ldquo;</span><strong>Transfer Notice</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) to each of the other Shareholders (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Continuing Shareholders</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) of the details of the proposed transfer including, in particular, the number of shares to be transferred (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Offer Shares</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Transfer Notice must offer the Offer Shares for sale to each of the Continuing Shareholders pro rata to the number of Relevant Shares held by each Continuing Shareholder (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Pro-Rata Offer</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) or to one of the Continuing Shareholders only (in the event that the other Continuing Shareholder declines the offer contained in the Transfer Notice) (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Alternative Offer</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) at a price determined in accordance with Clause 14.6 and / or 14.10. The Transfer Notice must also state the period within which the offer to sell the Offer Shares to the Continuing Shareholders shall remain open to be accepted. This period must be at least thirty Business Days from the date of the Transfer Notice (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Acceptance Period</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Continuing Shareholder may not accept the Alternative Offer if he has declined the Pro-Rata Offer.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">On receipt of a Transfer Notice each Continuing Shareholder may:</span></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">send a written notice to the Seller (an &ldquo;</span><strong>Acceptance Notice</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) within the Acceptance Period accepting the Pro-Rata Offer set out in the Transfer Notice and indicating whether or not he would be willing to accept the Alternative Offer in the event that the other Continuing Shareholder declines the Pro-Rata Offer;&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">send a written notice to the selling Shareholder within the Acceptance Period declining the Pro-Rata Offer; or</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">not reply to the Transfer Notice within the Acceptance Period. In this case, the Continuing Shareholder shall be deemed not to have accepted the Pro-Rata Offer or the Alternative Offer.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Pro-Rata Offer is accepted by the Continuing Shareholders within the Acceptance Period, the Continuing Shareholders will have the right to buy the Seller&rsquo;s Offer Shares on a pro-rata basis, according to the number of Relevant Shares held by the Continuing Shareholders on the date of the Transfer Notice at a price to be determined between the parties (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Offer Price</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;), or in default of agreeing the Offer Price, at the Fair Value of the shares determined in accordance with Clause 14.9.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Pro-Rata Offer is accepted by one Continuing Shareholder only, and that Continuing Shareholder has also accepted the Alternative Offer, that Continuing Shareholder will have the right to buy all of the Seller&rsquo;s Offer Shares at the Offer Price, or in default of agreeing the Offer Price, at the Fair Value of the shares determined in accordance with Clause 14.9.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Pro-Rata Offer is accepted by one Continuing Shareholder only, and that Continuing Shareholder has declined the Alternative Offer, that Continuing Shareholder shall have the right to buy the same number of shares from the Seller that it would had the right to if all Continuing Shareholders had accepted the Pro-Rata Offer as per Clause 14.5 and the Company shall then have the right for a period of one month commencing on the date on which the Acceptance Period ends to elect to purchase, subject to the provisions of the Companies Act, the remaining Offer Shares&nbsp; at the Offer Price or in default of agreeing the Offer Price, at the Fair Value. If the Company elects to purchase the remaining Offer Shares as aforesaid, it shall have a further period of 42 days in which to comply with the requirements of the Companies Act in regard thereto. If the Company does not elect to purchase the remaining Offer Shares within one month of the date on which the Acceptance Period ends, or does so elect but fails to comply with the said requirements of the Companies Act and purchase the remaining Offer Shares within the further 42 day period, then the Company shall be deemed to have refused to purchase the remaining Offer Shares. In that event, or in the event that the Company informs the Seller that that it does not wish to purchase the remaining Offer Shares, the Seller may sell the remaining Offer Shares to a third party, provided that such Offer Shares are not sold at less than Fair Value and the Seller shall be obliged to execute and deliver to the Company such further stamped instruments of transfer and ancillary documentation as may be required in order to effect the transfer of the legal and beneficial ownership of the shares to the third party free of encumbrances in accordance with the Constitution.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Pro-Rata Offer is not accepted by either Continuing Shareholder, the Company shall then have the right for a period of one month commencing on the date on which the Acceptance Period ends to elect to purchase, subject to the provisions of the Companies Act, the Offer Shares at the Offer Price or in default of agreeing the Offer Price, at the Fair Value. If the Company elects to purchase the Offer Shares as aforesaid, it shall have a further period of 42 days in which to comply with the requirements of the Companies Act in regard thereto. If the Company does not elect to purchase the Offer Shares within one month of the date on which the Acceptance Period ends, or does so elect but fails to comply with the said requirements of the Companies Act and purchase the Offer Shares within the further 42 day period, then the Company shall be deemed to have refused to purchase the Offer Shares. In that event, or in the event that the Company informs the Seller that that it does not wish to purchase the Offer Shares, the Seller&nbsp; may sell the Offer Shares to a third party, provided that such Offer Shares are not sold at less than Fair Value and the Seller shall be obliged to execute and deliver to the Company such further stamped instruments of transfer and ancillary documentation as may be required in order to effect the transfer of the legal and beneficial ownership of the shares to the third party free of encumbrances in accordance with the Constitution.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event that, there has been acceptance by one or all of the Continuing Shareholders and the Seller and a Continuing Shareholder cannot agree the Offer Price for the shares or in the event that the Company is to purchase some or all of the Offer Shares, the Fair Value of the shares to be sold in the Company shall be the value that the Expert certifies to be the fair market value in his opinion based on the following assumptions:</span></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the value of the shares in question is that proportion of the fair market value of the entire issued share capital of the Company that the Seller's shares bear to the then total issued share capital of the Company (with no premium or discount for the size of the Seller's shareholding or for the rights or restrictions applying to the shares);</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the sale is between a willing buyer and a willing seller on the open market;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the shares are to be valued as at the date of the Transfer Notice;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the Company is then carrying on its business as a going concern, on the assumption that it shall continue to do so; and</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the shares are sold free of all encumbrances.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event that the Seller and a Continuing Shareholder cannot agree an Offer Price and the Seller does not wish to transfer the Offer Shares to a Continuing Shareholder at a Fair Value calculated in accordance with Clause 14.9, the Seller may withdraw the offer to sell to the Continuing Shareholders and will be under no obligation to sell the Offer Shares to that Continuing Shareholder.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Seller withdraws their offer to the Continuing Shareholders in accordance with Clause 14.10 or if the Pro Rata Offer is not accepted by any Continuing Shareholders and if the Company does not elect to purchase the Offer Shares within the period referred to in Clause 14.8, the Seller may sell the Offer Shares to a third party within a period of not more than two months from the date that the Company does not elect to so purchase the Offer Shares at a price that is not less than the Fair Value.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No Shareholder shall Transfer or Dispose of any Share or any legal and/or equitable interest in any Share other than in accordance with this Agreement. Should a person become entitled to any Shares in consequence of the death or bankruptcy of any individual Shareholder or in any other circumstances who is not within the class of permitted transferees set out in Clause 14 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dealing in Shares</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">), Clause 15 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compulsory Transfers &ndash; Drag Along</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">), and Clause 16 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compulsory Transfers &ndash; Tag Along</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) and&nbsp; (a &ldquo;</span><strong>Prohibited Transferee</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) such person shall notify the Company of that fact, whereupon the Company shall notify the other Shareholders within one month of the date of receipt of such notice from the Prohibited Transferee.&nbsp; The other Shareholders shall have the right for a period of two months from the date of receipt of the notice from the Company to elect to purchase, pro rata to their existing holding of Relevant Shares, all but not some of the Shares held by the Prohibited Transferee or to which the Prohibited Transferee shall have become entitled at a price per share equal to the Fair Value.&nbsp; In the event that not all of the other Shareholders elect to purchase the Shares of the Prohibited Transferee (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Acquiring Shareholders</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;), the Acquiring Shareholders shall be entitled to acquire all but not some of the Shares of the Prohibited Transferee pro rata to the Relevant Shares held between those Acquiring Shareholders only, at a price per Share equal to the Fair Value.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If none of the other Shareholders elect to purchase the Shares held by the Prohibited Transferee, the Company shall have the right for a period of one month commencing on the date which is 3 months after the date of the receipt by it of the notice from the Prohibited Transferee referred to at Clause 14.12 hereof to elect to purchase, subject to the provisions of the Companies Act all but not some of the Shares held by the Prohibited Transferee at a price per share equal to the Fair Value.&nbsp; If the Company elects to purchase said Shares as aforesaid, it shall have a further period of 42 days in which to comply with the requirements of the Companies Act in regard thereto.&nbsp; If the Company shall fail to comply with the said requirements of the Companies Act and purchase the said Shares within the said period, then the Company shall be deemed to have refused to purchase the Shares held by the Prohibited Transferee and the Prohibited Transferee shall, on condition that he shall execute a deed confirming to the other Shareholders that he shall be bound by this Agreement as a Shareholder in the form set out in Schedule 2 hereof, be registered as a member of the Company, and the Company shall have no liability or obligation to the Prohibited Transferee on account of its original election to purchase his Shares.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Transfer or Disposal of any Share in accordance with this Clause 14 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dealing in Shares</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) shall be on the following condition: the transferee shall execute a deed confirming to the other Shareholders that he shall be bound by this Agreement as a Shareholder in respect of each Share transferred in the form set out in Schedule 2 hereto.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Each Shareholder shall procure that the Board only approves for registration a Transfer or Disposal of Shares carried out in accordance with this Agreement and the Constitution.&nbsp;</span></li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>COMPULSORY TRANSFERS &ndash; DRAG ALONG</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If an offer (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Offer</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) is made to acquire the entire issued share capital of the Company as part of a bona fide arm&rsquo;s length transaction and any Shareholder or group of Shareholders constituting in aggregate more than 80% of the Shares of the Company (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Proposing Shareholders</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) wish to accept the Offer in respect of their shares (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Selling Shares</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) the Proposing Shareholders shall have the right to give to the Company not less than 28 days&rsquo; advance notice before selling the Selling Shares.&nbsp; That notice (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Selling Notice</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) will include details of the Selling Shares and the proposed price for each Selling Share to be paid by the proposed purchaser (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Proposed Purchaser</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;), details of the Proposed Purchaser, the place, date and time of completion of the proposed purchase being a date not less than 28 days from the date of the Selling Notice (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Compulsory Sale</strong> <strong>Completion</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Immediately upon receipt of the Selling Notice, the Board shall give notice in writing (a &ldquo;</span><strong>Compulsory Sale Notice</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) to each of the shareholders (other than the Proposing Shareholders) of the Company giving the details contained in the Selling Notice and requiring them each to sell to the Proposed Purchaser at the Compulsory Sale Completion all of their holding of shares.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Each Shareholder who is given a Compulsory Sale Notice shall, in the event of a sale, sell all of his Shares referred to in the Compulsory Sale Notice at the highest price and same terms per Selling Share proposed to be sold to the Proposed Purchaser on the Compulsory Sale Completion by the Proposing Shareholders.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If any of the Shareholders fail to comply with the terms of Clause 15.3 (&ldquo;</span><strong>Defaulting Shareholder(s)</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;), the Company shall be constituted the agent of each of the Defaulting Shareholders for the sale of their shares in accordance with the Compulsory Sale Notice (together with all rights then attached thereto) and the Board may authorise some person to execute and deliver on behalf of each of the Defaulting Shareholders the necessary transfer(s) and the Company may receive the purchase money in trust for each of the Defaulting Shareholders and cause the Proposed Purchaser to be registered as the holder of such shares. The receipt of the Company for the purchase money, pursuant to such transfers, shall constitute a good and valid discharge to the Proposed Purchaser (who shall not be bound to see the application thereof) and after the Proposed Purchaser has been registered in purported exercise of the aforesaid powers the validity of the proceedings shall not be questioned by any person. The Company shall not pay the purchase money to a Defaulting Shareholder until he shall, in respect of the shares being the subject of the Compulsory Sale Notice, have delivered his share certificates or a suitable indemnity and the necessary transfers to the Company.&nbsp; The Proposing Shareholders shall sell the Selling Shares to the Proposed Purchaser on the Compulsory Sale Completion, subject at all times to the Proposed Purchaser being able to withdraw the Selling Notice at any time prior to the Compulsory Sale Completion by giving notice to the Company to that effect, whereupon each Compulsory Sale Notice shall no longer be binding and shall cease to have effect.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board may require to be satisfied that the shares to be sold by the Proposing Shareholders are to be sold bona fide for the consideration stated in the Selling Notice without any deduction, rebate or allowance whatsoever to the Proposed Purchaser and if not so satisfied may require the proposed price to be determined by the Expert.&nbsp; The Company may request that the Expert determine and certify the sum, which in their opinion, is the fair market price of a share in the Company (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Fair Market Price</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) as at the date of the Compulsory Sale Notice.&nbsp; For the purposes of determining the Fair Market Price, the Expert shall have regard to the same assumptions that are set out in Clause 14.9.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board and the Proposing Shareholders shall give to the Expert all information in their possession which a prudent prospective purchaser of the whole of the share capital of the Company might reasonably require if he were to purchase the same from a willing vendor by private treaty on arm&rsquo;s length terms. The cost of obtaining any Experts&rsquo; certificate (including any expert valuations required in respect thereof) shall be borne by the Company.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">This Clause 15 shall apply </span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">mutatis mutandis</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;"> where:</span></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">(the Offer referred to in Clause 15.1 is an offer to acquire all or substantially all of the assets of the Company rather than the entire issued share capital of the Company; or</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the Proposing Shareholders referred to in Clause 15.1 wish to procure the flotation of the Company on a recognised stock exchange rather than accept an Offer.</span></li>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Transfer of any Share in accordance with this Clause 15 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compulsory Transfers &ndash; Drag </span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Along) shall be on the following condition:&nbsp;</span></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the transferee shall execute a deed confirming to the other Shareholders that he shall be bound by this Agreement as a Shareholder in respect of each Share transferred in the form set out in Schedule 2 hereto; and</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the Proposed Purchaser will procure the redemption of all of the Redeemable Preference Shares then in issue on or before Compulsory Sale Completion.</span></li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>COMPULSORY TRANSFERS &ndash; TAG ALONG</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If any Shareholder or any Connected Person of such Shareholder (collectively, a &ldquo;</span><strong>Selling Shareholder</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) intends to Transfer or Dispose (whether in one or a series of transactions) shares constituting an aggregate of more than 40% of the Shares then held by him, such Selling Shareholder shall, subject always to observing all provisions of the Constitution, follow the procedures set out in this Clause 16 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compulsory Transfers &ndash; Tag Along</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Where the provisions of Clause 16.1 apply, the relevant Selling Shareholder shall give to the Company not less than 28 days&rsquo; notice in advance of such proposed sale (a &ldquo;</span><strong>Sale Notice</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;), specifying in such Sale Notice the identity of the proposed purchaser (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Buyer</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;), the price per share which the Buyer is proposing to pay, the manner in which the consideration is to be paid, and the maximum number of Shares which the relevant Selling Shareholder proposes to sell (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Selling Shareholder&rsquo;s Shares</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Forthwith upon receipt by the Company of a Sale Notice from the Selling Shareholder, the Company shall send a copy of the Sale Notice to all members (other than the Selling Shareholders) of the Company.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Each Shareholder (other than the Selling Shareholders) shall be entitled, within 14 days after receipt of the copy of the Sale Notice, to notify the relevant Selling Shareholder that he (a &ldquo;</span><strong>Tag-Along Shareholder</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) wishes to sell any Shares held by that Tag-Along Shareholder (the &ldquo;</span><strong>Tag-Along Shares</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;) at the proposed sale price together with the Selling Shareholder (a &ldquo;</span><strong>Tag-Along Notice</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">&rdquo;).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Following receipt of a Tag-Along Notice from a Tag-Along Shareholder, the Selling Shareholder shall be entitled to sell to the Buyer (on the terms notified to the Company in the Sale Notice) the Selling Shareholder&rsquo;s Shares provided that at the same time the Buyer purchases the relevant Tag-Along Shares from each Tag-Along Shareholder on terms no less favourable than those obtained by the Selling Shareholder.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If no member gives any Tag-Along Notice pursuant to Clause 16.4 within the permitted time, or notifies the Selling Shareholder that it does not wish to sell any shares at the proposed price, then the Selling Shareholder shall be free to sell shares in accordance with the terms of the original Sale Notice.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No sale by the Selling Shareholder shall be made pursuant to any Sale Notice more than three months after service of that Sale Notice pursuant to Clause 16.2.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Transfer of any Share in accordance with this Clause 16 (</span><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Compulsory Transfers &ndash; Tag Along</span></em><span style="font-weight: 400;">) shall be on the following condition:&nbsp;</span></li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
    <ul>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the transferee shall execute a deed confirming to the other Shareholders that he shall be bound by this Agreement as a Shareholder in respect of each Share transferred in the form set out in Schedule 2 hereto; and&nbsp;</span></li>
    </ul>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>ALLOTMENT IN DEFAULT OF TAKING UP OF ENTITLEMENT</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">17.1</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Company wishes to issue further Shares, each of the Shareholders shall procure (so far as is lawfully possible in the exercise of its rights/his rights and powers as a Shareholder in the Company) that the Company offers, by giving written notice to each Shareholder, that each Shareholder is entitled to that proportion of the Shares proposed to be issued which the number of Shares held by that Shareholders bears to the total number of ordinary Shares in issue at the time the Company gives its notice </span><strong>("Shareholder Entitlement"</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">). Such offer shall state the number of Shares to be issued and the price of the Shares.</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">17.2</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Each Shareholder may accept the offer by giving notice to the Company, at any time within ten (ten) business days following the Company&rsquo;s notice, accompanied by payment to the Company in cleared funds of the full payment for the Shares to be subscribed for. Each Shareholder shall also be asked by the Company to indicate if it would be willing to take up excess Shares over and above its Shareholders Entitlements in the event that a Shareholder does not wish to acquire its Shareholder Entitlement.</span></p>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">17.3</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Any Shares referred to in the Company&rsquo;s offer, for which the Shareholders do not subscribe, may be issued by the Company to any Shareholders who indicated they would be willing to take up shares in excess of their Shareholder Entitlement. Such Shares will be allocated pro rata amongst those Shareholders according to the proportion which the number of Shares held by those Shareholders bears to the total number of Shares held by the Shareholders who wish to take up an excess over their Shareholder Entitlement.&nbsp; Any Shares which are not subscribed for after the offers under this section may be issued by the Company as it thinks fit, provided that any such issue is completed within (20) business days after the Company&rsquo;s notice of the offer.</span></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>ALLOCATION OF SHARES TO XXX</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <ol>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The following provisions shall only apply to the transfer of Shares from XXX to XXX.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Board shall agree a set of annual financial and performance targets for the Company within 30 days of the start of each Financial Year. The Board and the Auditors shall determine whether the Company achieved its financial and performance targets for each Financial Year within 30 days of the start of the following Financial Year.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event that the Board and the Auditors determine that the Company equals or exceeds its financial and performance targets set for a Financial Year XXX shall transfer 10 per cent of its shareholding to XXX as a performance incentive.&nbsp; The Shares shall be transferred to XXX for nominal value within 30 days of the determination being made by the Board and the Auditors that the Company equalled or exceeded its financial and performance targets. In the event that the Company does not equal or exceed the financial and performance targets for a Financial Year then XXX shall retain the entirety of its shareholding and no shares shall be transferred to XXX as a performance incentive.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The provisions of clause 18.2 shall continue to operate each year until such time as XXX shall obtain a Shareholding of 90% of the issued Shares in the Company.</span></li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">18.5</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">XXX shall not be required to transfer any further Shares to XXX pursuant to clause 18.2 in circumstances where its shareholding has been reduced to an amount equal to 10 per cent of the issued Shares in the Company.</span></p>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>DEADLOCK</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a dispute between the Shareholders as per Clause 10.6 or an unresolved deadlock of the Directors as per Clause 8.2, remaining unresolved for a further period of fifteen Business Days, any Director or Shareholder (as the case may be) may nominate an independent third party, acceptable to the Directors, to act as a mediator to assist them to resolve the matter. In the event that the Directors cannot agree on a mediator within five Business Days of the first nomination of a mediator, the mediator shall be a third party nominated by the President of the Law Society of Ireland.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the deadlock cannot still be resolved all of the Directors or Shareholders will agree to the appointment of another independent director, the identity of such independent director is to be agreed by the Directors or Shareholders in dispute (as the case may be).</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event that the Directors or Shareholders cannot agree on the identity of such independent Director, the independent Director to be appointed will be chosen by the Auditors.&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The matter to be resolved will be put before all of the Directors, including the new Director. The Directors will vote on the issue and it will be resolved on the basis of one vote per Director.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If a resolution or disposition is not agreed in accordance with the provisions of Clauses 19.1 &ndash; 19.4 within 35 Business Days of such deadlock the following provisions shall apply:</span></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Any Shareholder may send a notice to the Directors requiring them to convene a general meeting of the Company to be held immediately at short notice to consider resolutions to sell the Business or conduct a Sale. The Shareholders shall take all necessary action to ensure that the general meeting is held at short notice. At this general meeting, a Shareholder shall not vote against the resolution to sell the Company unless all the other Shareholders present at the meeting agree.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If a resolution to sell the Company is passed, the Shareholders shall pass a resolution appointing an independent corporate finance firm to realise the maximum value of the Company for the Shareholders, whether by way of sale of the Business or a Sale.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Shareholders do not agree on an independent corporate finance firm any Shareholder may request the President of the Law Society to make the appointment on such terms as he thinks fit.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Shareholders shall make all reasonable efforts to facilitate the realisation of the maximum value of the Company by the independent corporate finance firm.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the independent corporate finance firm is unable to obtain a sale of the Business or a Sale within 180 days of the date of their appointment, then any Shareholder may send a notice to the Directors requiring them to convene a general meeting of the Company to be held immediately at short notice to consider resolutions to wind-up the Company and upon that resolution being passed, to appoint a liquidator. The Shareholders shall take all necessary action to ensure that the general meeting is held at short notice. At this general meeting, a Shareholder shall not vote against the resolution to wind-up the Company and to appoint a liquidator unless all the other Shareholders present at the meeting agree.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If a resolution to wind-up the Company is passed, the Shareholders shall pass a resolution appointing a liquidator to wind-up the Company.</span></li>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the Shareholders do not agree on a liquidator any Shareholder may request the President of the Law Society to make the appointment on such terms as he thinks fit.&nbsp;</span></li>
    </ol>
    </ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>NON COMPETE</strong></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Each of the Shareholders further covenants with and undertakes to the Company:</span></li>
    <ol>
    <li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">to not during the Restricted Period directly or indirectly within the Restricted Business Area (and whether from a place of business within or outside the Restricted Business Area) carry on or be interested in any Restricted Business or otherwise compete with the Company;&nbsp;</span></li>
